Just wanted to update you on the yearbook. Now that graduation is done, the yearbook has been finalized and submitted. We are looking at a 6-7 week arrival. So, the yearbooks should be at the school by the time school is in session. If you haven't ordered one, there is still time! The flat rate for a yearbook is 19.50, we accept cash or check. Please feel free to email Mrs. Ries, the yearbook advisor if you are interested!
Thank you for supporting Henry School!
Sincerely,
Mrs. Ries

First of all, we would like to thank you all for the support during school closure. It was hectic for all of us and the district is very thankful for everything all of you did during this time.

School is officially out. Grades have been posted on infinite campus. Please check your campus parent accounts to access grades. If you need a physical copy of a report card, please contact the school or email one of our dean of students matt.mohr@k12.sd.us and tyler.grassel@k12.sd.us

post_text:
Hello Everyone! We are getting closer to our start date! As enrollments have come in, we have come to the conclusion that we are NOT having the seperate days anymore. Your children would be allowed to attend every day of the week. If your child does not have a Mask, we are planning on making some at the program for your children to use there.

Like last summer, snacks are provided but you must bring your own lunch. Hours are from 8am-4pm.

If you have any questions or concerns, please dont hesitate to reach out. This is a very crazy time, but we are going to do what is safest for your children and our staff. We are ready to see some familiar faces again!

Here is the link for the enrollment form. Please fill this out and return back to Michaela.Meinders@k12.sd.us - If you aren't able to send back with me, please let me know that you plan to send with your children to the program. https://docs.google.com/document/d/1W2af1oyz3Sn5sfgluAytaZROCGeKBWIUUqndXTOgw6A/mobilebasic

Thank you!!

post_text:
Hello all!

I hope you had a great weekend!

This is a reminder to all students and parents to please continue doing work at this time. I know it is hectic and we all have different environments, but keep your heads up. Ask your teachers questions! If you have any issues whether it be connectivity or anything please contact the school. The best way to get ahold of people is by using email.

Also, we know there is a lot going on. If you are having any issues at all reach out. We are here for you. Although our building is closed, our educators are not. We are working many hours to get you as much information as possible. Please contact anyone and we will assist.

Reminder food package request can be done on our website and our Facebook page from the post on April 3rd. It is the same link each week. Pickup is still Thursday from 3 to 5 pm.

Thank you all!

We miss you, we can't wait to see all of you. Until next time have a great day, hug your kids, tell them you love them!

Respectfully,

Philip Schonebaum

post_text:
Good Morning Henry Family, As we approach the weekend, I wanted to take a moment and share a video that was made by Jostens Renaissance company. Our students have had the opportunity to listen to Mr. Mike Smith talk in Watertown and also at the state student council convention in Rapid City. Mike Smith's message in this video is something I think we all need to hear at this time.

https://www.jostensrenaissance.com/

I believe that we can all become stronger through this timeframe. If we all use this time to be better at what we are doing and make an impact on each other when we are all through this, this time will not be wasted.

Once again, thank you Henry Family for all you are doing at this time and we cannot wait to see students roaming our halls soon.

Have a great weekend!

Respectfully,

Philip Schonebaum

Good Morning Henry Family,

I hope the first week of remote learning is going well for your children. I know we will all get through this and learn weekly. As you all have heard from my school reach earlier this week school is officially out until May 4th. The teachers will be getting together on Tuesday to discuss our first week of remote learning. If there is any feedback or issues related to this, don't hesitate to email philip.schonebaum@k12.sd.us.
Teachers have compiled initial items on a google doc. That is still accessible. It does have teacher emails in this doc

https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1pwGolLg7K4wz36BCVTEcYfggdVInkuO3vGK_IsbJ4dc/edit?usp=sharing

If you are having trouble with a subject matter, please reach out to your teacher and schedule a meeting. Teachers are providing resources to help with lessons while they are away. All teachers have home offices set up to help at this time.

Thanks all!

If there is anything I can help you with, please reach out.

Respectfully,

Philip Schonebaum

post_text:
Good Morning and I hope you are enjoying your weekend. This week has been full of ups and downs, but there is nothing better than having added time with your kids! We miss them here at school and will be excited to get them back, but until then, keep hugging them, telling them you love them, and providing structured activities to challenge and help them grow. (I am writing this after losing three straight games of UNO with my five year old...I think he is cheating.)

Reminder on Tuesday we have distribution of materials for distance education. Ask teachers times that they will be available to answer questions during the day. They are currently finding ways to make themselves available to their students. Distribution schedule is: 8 to 9 am A-G last names, 9 to 10 am H-Q last names and 10 to 11 am R-Z last names.

Also, we are doing another meal distribution on Thursday from 3 to 5 pm. Sign up is below.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdvaI2oaPvnvuCEnJbfh8zeQGqz20OUGwBBEpgDNQZuBGzOYA/viewform?usp=sf_link

You can also sign up on the website.

Thanks all!

post_text:
Good Morning Henry Family,

We are currently working on plans for if this closure ends up being very long term. Those plans include how to get supplemental education materials for our students, how to provide the potential for sack lunches, and how to ensure that the integrity of our education stays intact. The Department of Health and Department of Education will be holding conference calls this week with superintendents to help them make decisions. Please be patient as we make decisions for the positive impact of all of our students.

This is new for all of us and we must come together in this process. I plan on sending a school reach tomorrow afternoon with more information. If you see a missed call from the school, it will be a school reach call with more information.

Stay safe, hug your children, spend time with them during this time!

Have a great week and I will update you when I receive more direction from our government officials.

Respectfully,

Philip Schonebaum

post_text:
It is that time of year where school years are starting the last quarter. With the change of seasons, many families start thinking of their school choice and where their students will be attending school in the fall. Henry School is a great choice for your educational endeavors. We feature an elite fine arts program that has received multiple awards. An extraordinary student council that will be named "outstanding" by the state of South Dakota for the 5th year in a row. A new Esports team that students will learn STEM, teamwork, and social skills throughout. This spring we will also enter the South Dakota Trap Shooting League.

We have it all in Henry and we have it all when it comes to a highly motivated, highly caring, dedicated, loving staff. We invite you to come to Henry and see what it is all about. We are now taking inquiries for the Fall semester. Don't miss your chance to be a part of this great district. "Building Relationships. Empowering Learners." --Excellence Always.

The Below information is an invitation to all 5th-grade parents and family members. Please reserve your time this day to celebrate the Dare graduation of our 5th Grade class.

Dear Parent or Guardian, February 19, 2020

You are invited to join the Henry School in honoring our Fifth-Grade students that participated and completed the D.A.R.E. program. We are having a graduation ceremony on Tuesday, March 3rd at 2:30 PM in the afternoon with a short presentation from Deputy Steve Lowry. Following the ceremony, you are welcome to stay and enjoy the cake and juice with your child. We look forward to seeing you and hope that you can join in the celebration.



Vikki Larson
Secretary
Henry School District
Phone: 605-532-5364
Fax: 605-532-3795

We are thankful for our partnership with Avera! A huge thank you to Vikki Larson for being the hands for our E-nurse.

Good morning Henry Family,

I hope all of you are enjoying the start of your long holiday weekend. We look forward to school resuming on Tuesday, February 18th. This is a reminder notification that school is in session on Friday, February 21. The snow makeup day for last week is scheduled for Friday, February 28th. So we will be in session the next two Fridays for school.

In addition, good luck to our girls basketball team in the Warner classic this afternoon vs. Sully Buttes. It should be a great game!

Have a great weekend and we look forward to seeing all of the students back in the school on Tuesday!

Respectfully,

Philip Schonebaum
Superintendent of Henry School

post_text:
Good Evening Henry Family,

Due to the wind chill warning and forecasted temps falling within the range of our wind chill policy. Henry will start 2 hours late tomorrow, February 13th. We will continually monitor wind chills in the morning to ensure the safety of all of our students, faculty, and stakeholders that may have to venture out in the extreme cold. On all 2 hour late starts we do not serve breakfast at the school. Please ensure your child has been fed before sending them on the bus. NTHS REPORT AT 9:45 am

In addition, the time has been set for the makeup board meeting. The Henry School Board will meet at 4:30 pm tomorrow February 13th.

Have a great night, Stay Safe and Stay Warm.

The Henry School will be closed tomorrow February 12 due to the Blizzard Warning issued by the National Weather Service. Safety is our number one priority for students, faculty, and stakeholders. In addition, the board meeting scheduled for tomorrow night has been postponed to Thursday. The time has not been determined. We will post a time on the website and social media tomorrow when time can be determined. A makeup snow date will be announced after the next school board meeting.

Stay Safe and Stay Warm.

Respectfully,

Philip Schonebaum

The one act play had their strongest performance yet at State! They performed at Sioux Falls O’Gorman, Thursday afternoon for a crowd of around 400 people. They came away with 5 superior performer awards: Destinee Nelson, Collins Fuller, Chase Kelly, Jaden Thomas and Olivia Nelson.

The students all did a fantastic job and our judges had many positive comments! This was definitely a memorable experience!

If you see any of the students involved or if you see the director Mrs. Martens, give them a congratulations. They have been an absolute force this year in fine arts!

post_text:
The students pictured participated in the State Tournament!
They all received the highest honor in their performances.
They are holding an equivalent to a state championship in their hands: The Oral Interp Team of Excellence award.

Rachel Blue, DeLaney Anderson, Collin Fuller and Chase Kelly received a Superior on their Reader’s Theater, “Election Day”
Collin Fuller received a superior on his humorous piece, “A Triune Tale of Diminutive Swine”.
Chase Kelly and Collin Fuller received a superior on their duet, “Assault Toast”.

A superior is the highest rating students are able to receive at State Oral Interp. We also received a team excellence award.
I attached a picture taken yesterday of the students with their medals and the team excellence award we received.
There were also pictures of the students I sent in the e-mails this past weekend.

These students worked very hard and represented our school very well at State Oral Interp earning all superiors!

Anyone that has volunteered to bring baked goods or is planning to bring baked goods for the Bake Sale, there will be a few different times when you can drop off your baked goods.

Friday: 8am-3pm
Saturday: 3pm-4pm (approx.)
Sunday: 10am-Bake sale starts at 12

Friday or Sunday preferably works better, but if you are needing to drop off on Saturday, please let me know so we can make specific arrangements.

You can either bring them individually wrapped or a few put on plates. It doesn't matter either way for us. We will just price them when they come. What ever way is easier for you, works for us!

Thank you again to everyone that is willing to bring in goodies to support the program! You have no idea how much it means to us all!

shared_text:
Henry Student Council
September 24, 2019 at 10:25 PM ·

Henry StuCo is incredibly grateful this evening. To those of you that provided direct support in making Coronation 2019 happen, we THANK YOU!

Homecoming is always a bit of a whirlwind, and it feels terrific having a SOLID group of people that provide a backbone for our intentions. As many of tonights candidates stated, "Henry = family", and we felt it this evening.

Whether you provided material things, or offered your time and effort, YOU are appreciated and we couldn't do it without you. Many of you took a second to thank me tonight, but take a look in the mirror and grin, because you have yourselves to thank as well; not to mention the sweat poured into our events by StuCo members.

To the spectators and active participants in food eating competitions, tug of war, and lip sync performances, you are rockstars!

To the candidates, thank you for your positive attitudes and unique characteristics. This evening was about you and we hope you enjoyed it.

And finally, to Jason and CaLeigh: CONGRATULATIONS! Your crowns complement those beaming smiles well, and we are happy for you!

Today our wonderful staff officially start the school year. The staff will be in in-service today learning and growing so they can impact your children. We believe that all children can learn and that all children deserve the best education possible. As a staff, we will ensure we build positive life lasting relationships so we can empower your kids to learn at their highest level.

If you see a teacher thank them for their dedication to your child! We can't wait to get this wonderful staff back in the building to continue growing the minds of our Henry Youth!

"Building Relationships. Empowering Learners." Excellence Always.

Don't forget about our open house this week 4 to 7 pm on Wednesday!! All are invited. You do not need a child in the school to attend. Come and see the school and say HELLO! If you are thinking about being apart of Henry, don't hesitate to set up an appointment.

Welcome Back to another great school year!

As school nears, I wanted to reach out and thank all of the community teams that came together to make the Henry Before and After School Program and Summer Program so successful this last year. Ms. Johnson and Ms. Ulschmid have worked extremely hard with the youth to continue to develop and grow the talented learners in our school district. We look forward to seeing this program grow and build students throughout the year. The After School Program will start on the first day of school this year. It is open to all Henry students PK-12. We hope that your child sincerely thinks about signing up and participating. WIth that school will be here before we know it. Check out our Back to School information on our school website. We appreciate your dedication and it is our pleasure to continue to help serve and care for your children in our district.

Thank you,
Philip Schonebaum

Just like that, career week is over! To finish off the week, we had a Codington County Investigator come to visit us! He showed the kids his vehicle and talked to them about the different things he does during his job!

Later, Travis Purdy, who is an Army Soldier, visited with the kids about what it takes to be a soldier! They all enjoyed trying on all of the gear he brought!

We would like to thank everyone again that had talked to our kids about their careers! It was a GREAT week!

post_text:
Another wonderful day during Career Week!!

We had Jim & Lucas Johnson from Johnson Trucking in Clark (Miss Johnson's Family) come to visit us! They brought 2 different trailers for the kids to learn all about! I don't know what they liked better..climbing in the trailer or honking the horn!

We also had Paul Johnson come to visit with the kids all about Farming! They got to learn about the different grains and what happens to them when they are harvested! Both real life jobs around our area!

Thank you to Jim, Lucas & Paul for coming in today! The kids had a BLAST!!

The Henry School has revamped our graduation requirements throughout last year. Any student Grade 11 and lower will be impacted by these changes. The graduation requirements have changed from 22 to 25 graduation credits and there are three paths Basic High School Diploma, Advanced Endorsement, and Advanced Honors Endorsement. There is more information on our website under the graduation requirements tab. At this year's open house on August 14, we will have a meeting requiring all students to sign up for their pathways. Please SAVE THAT DATE.

Thank you for your continued support of the Henry District.

post_text: On Thursday Quentyn H. had the opportunity to be the principal for the day as a reward for reading almost 500 AR points! He helped Mr. Redmond throughout the day by greeting students as they came into school for the morning, making up a rule for the 4th graders, and talking about what things he likes most about the Henry school. He wanted more time to read and less math, if you can believe that! He also learned that the most important part of being a principal is drinking a lot of coffee, but Quentyn stuck to his chocolate milk. Congrats Quentyn!

post_text: The After School Program has recently implemented a spelling program. Every week, they have been practicing their spelling words. Their reward is a FREE McDonald's Happy Meal! All they have to do to earn the Happy Meal is be in attendance at least 1 day a week and earn a 100% on their spelling test in the week they attended. When they earn 4 100%'s, they earn their FREE Happy Meal! How great is that!? We have 4 that have earned theirs! Congrats to these kiddos! Great Job!

post_text:
The Henry School District's mission is simple. "Building Relationships. Empowering Learners." We believe that students that have positive relationships at school will be more focused to learn during the school day and outside of school. Relationships are extremely important to our staff in Henry. If you want to look at a school that embodies their mission statement and believes they can make a change in every student, look no further.

The Henry School believes in academics and the board recently raised graduation requirements to 25 credits. We believe students should be in school and engaged. We want to ensure that we create life long learners that will contribute to our 21st-century global society.

If you would like a tour of the Henry School or to open enroll, please contact the school at 532-5364 or email either the building principal jon.redmond@k12.sd.us or the superintendent philip.schonebaum@k12.sd.us

post_text:
Update from the Music Department/Music Teacher Deanna Martens:

This summer we have 3 students from Henry that will be part of the South Dakota Ambassadors of Music. They will be going on a concert tour of Europe from June 27th – July 12th, visiting and performing in 7 countries (England, France, Switzerland, Liechtenstein, Austria, Italy, Germany) in 16 days! These students include DeLaney Anderson, Desi Nelson and Rachel Blue. There will be a farewell concert at SDSU on June 26th.

They are currently working hard preparing their music. DeLaney and Rachel will be part of the band and Desi will be a member of the choir.

How awesome to have such a wonderful representation from our school! Wish them well on their exciting summer!

Thank you, girls, for representing the Henry School!
